The paper deals with computer vision and optimization algorithms, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of prior knowledge and statistical information also suggests a possible fit in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The evaluation of results for driving scenes suggests a possible fit in the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of sparse measurements and interpolation suggests a possible fit in the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
